http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Sat 27 Aug 2011
Source: The Taipei Times, Central News Agency (CNA) [edited]
http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/taiwan/archives/2011/08/28/2003511870


Hospital transplants organs of donors infected with HIV
-------------------------------------------------------
The National Taiwan University Hospital transplanted the organs of a
donor infected with HIV [human immunodeficiency virus] on Wednesday
(24 Aug 2011) without realizing it, putting 5 organ transplant
recipients at high risk of contracting AIDS [acquired immunodeficiency
syndrome], the Department of Health said yesterday (Fri 26 Aug 2011).
The department said it was the first-ever known incident of recipients
being exposed to the risk of contracting AIDS because of organ
transplants.

The hospital informed the Health Department of the incident earlier in
the day, Centers for Disease Control deputy director Shih Wen-yi said.
Shih said the hospital had offered emergency anti-AIDS medication to
the 5 organ transplant recipients. The hospital has not issued a
statement on why the organs were not properly screened before the
transplant or when it actually discovered that the donor had HIV
infection. The Health Department has demanded that the hospital
present a full report on the incident within 3 days.

Shih said the hospital had apologized to the patients and their
families as well as briefing them on the situation. He added that to
the best of his knowledge, the hospital had consistently conducted HIV
testing on organ donors. "We don't know at the moment what went wrong
in this case, which has left 5 innocent organ recipients facing the
risk of contracting AIDS," Shih said.

