<promed@promedmail.org>

[Guidelines for preventing transmission of human immunodeficiency
virus through transplantation of human tissue and organs have been
published by the United States' Centers for Disease Control and
Prevention -- MMWR Recommendations and Reports 1994; 43(RR-8); 1-17,
20 May /(http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/00031670.htm).

The present incident in Taiwan appears to have been an unfortunate
consequence of a failure in communication rather than any technical
insufficiency. The outcome of the current investigation of the
incident is awaited. No doubt lessons will be learned. It remains to
be established in due course whether the emergency anti-AIDS
medications administered to these 5 organ transplant recipients will
be sufficient to prevent the establishment of HIV infection. - Mod.CP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Taiwan can be seen at
http://healthmap.org/r/00tD. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
